Spectral partitioning¶

Partitioning for the example in the lecture notes:

In [18]:
import numpy as np

L = np.array([[2, -1, -1, 0, 0], 
              [-1, 3, -1, 0, -1], 
              [-1, -1, 4, -1, -1],
              [0, 0, -1, 2, -1], 
              [0, -1, -1, -1, 3]])

vals, vects = np.linalg.eig(L)
order = vals.argsort()
vals = vals[order]
vects = vects[:, order]

with np.printoptions(precision=3, suppress=True):
    print(vals)
    print()
    print(vects)
